Package: ffTrack
Title: class for out-of-core GRanges based access for giant numeric genomic data
    tracks using ff package
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Author: Marcin Imielinski <mimielinski@nygenome.org>
Maintainer: Marcin Imielinski <mimielinski@nygenome.org>
Description: ffTrack allows building of objects of large genomically-indexed base-
    resolution sequence or numeric data for quasi-random out of memory access.
    ffTrack objects are indexable using GRanges from GenomicRanges package.
    Underlying files are written as .ffData objects using the ff package.
Imports:
    rtracklayer (>= 1.25),
    data.table,
    Biostrings,
    parallel,
    methods,
    GenomeInfoDb,
    S4Vectors,
    GenomicRanges (>= 1.18)
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.0),
    gUtils (>= 0.1),
    ff (>= 2.2)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1.9000
Suggests: testthat
